         <abstract>
            <p>Several widely used analytic forecasting models are tested on the earnings per share of a number of companies to determine the most effective predictive device. The poor performance of the selected models raises serious questions regarding the applicability of such techniques. Evidence is presented indicating that an econometric model may substantially improve the forecasts.</p>
         </abstract>
